A petrol tanker exploded Wednesday morning in Lokoja, the capital of Kogi State. The accident occurred along Felele – Nataco axis of Abuja – Lokoja road. Five cars, one tanker, three tricycles and two motorcycles were involved in the mishap. Some Kogi State Polytechnic students and Primary School pupils were burned. The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has confirmed 23 casualties. A family of six was consumed. Eleven bodies have been claimed by relatives, while the rest are in Kogi State Specialist morgue. Kogi State Government has expressed sadness and commiserated with those who knew the victims. <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-842351" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-3.jpg.webp" alt="" width="720" height="960" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-3.jpg.webp 720w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-3-225x300.jpg.webp 225w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"> <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-842352" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-2.jpg.webp" alt="" width="1560" height="2080" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-2.jpg.webp 1560w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-2-225x300.jpg.webp 225w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-2-768x1024.jpg.webp 768w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-2-1152x1536.jpg.webp 1152w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-2-1536x2048.jpg.webp 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 1560px) 100vw, 1560px"> <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-842353" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-1.jpg.webp" alt="" width="512" height="682" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-1.jpg.webp 512w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2020-09-23-1-225x300.jpg.webp 225w" sizes="(max-width: 512px) 10